            <h1 class="fontWeight400">Problem</h1>
            <h4>Checkout is the commitment layer of the marketplace journey. By the time users reach checkout, they are no longer trying to explore every option. They are trying to confirm the rental, resolve required logistics, pay, and know what happens next. </h4>
            <h4>The old checkout mixed order completion with account creation, optional prompts, and editing paths. This created extra opportunities for users to pause, hit errors, or leave after they had already shown purchase intent.</h4>

          </div>
